timeline.bodyText:
Instead of checking a field (which is set in another method), I suggest calling peek(), so that the knowledge of that field becomes more "local". To prevent the creation of Optional instances, we could create a private "peekNullable" (or any better name than that) method, which just returns null.
That would also allow the do ... while to be refactored to a while, which is generally considered cleaner:
while (peekNullable() == null && System.currentTimeMillis() < deadline) {
... wait for data
}
return peekNullable() != null;

